attribute.name: description
attribute.value: Although both Shrink AUR and Shrink Units are read-only, this rule holds two expressions. The reason is that this rule has to be seen in combination with the load/refresh rule. In the load rule the same expressions are being used to force a calculation of real Shrink AUR from loaded $ and Units for elapsed period. When the load rule group transitions to the calc rule group, the same identical rule is found and therefore not executed. Similar for the refresh rule, both Shrink U and Shrink $ get updated which forces the Shrink AUR expression in this rule to fire.

attribute.name: formula
attribute.value: BUWpBOPC = if ( current==first, BUWpBOSC, lag ( BUWpEOPC ) )

attribute.name: formula
attribute.value: BUWpBOPR = if ( current==first, BUWpBOSR, lag ( BUWpEOPR ) )

attribute.name: formula
attribute.value: BUWpBOPU = if ( current==first, BUWpBOSU, lag ( BUWpEOPU ) )

attribute.name: formula
attribute.value: BUWpEOPU = if (current == first, ignore, lead( BUWpBOPU))

attribute.name: formula
attribute.value: BUWpCMUP = ((tssum(BUWpBOSR,first,first) + tssum(BUWpRecR + BUWpMiscInR - BUWpMiscOutR + BUWpMkupR )) - (tssum(BUWpBOSC,first,first) + tssum(BUWpRecC + BUWpMiscInC - BUWpMiscOutC ))) / (tssum(BUWpBOSR,first,first) + tssum(BUWpRecR + BUWpMiscInR - BUWpMiscOutR + BUWpMkupR ))

attribute.name: description
attribute.value: BUWP Open To Buy U AUR

attribute.name: formula
attribute.value: BUWpEOPR = BUWpRecR + BUWpBOPR - BUWpSlsR - BUWpMkdR - BUWpShrinkR - BUWpMiscOutR + BUWpMiscInR + BUWpMkupR - BUWpInvAdjR

attribute.name: formula
attribute.value: BUWpRecR = BUWpEOPR - BUWpBOPR + BUWpSlsR + BUWpMkdR + BUWpShrinkR + BUWpMiscOutR - BUWpMiscInR - BUWpMkupR + BUWpInvAdjR

attribute.name: description
attribute.value: The calculation contains Markdown and Markup * 0 in order to have this expression trigger before the calculation kicks in which converts $ Receipts into U Receipts. If the Mkd * 0/ Mkup * 0 expressions are removed, a change to Mkd/Mkup will affect Receipt units but keep the Receipt AUR constant.

attribute.name: formula
attribute.value: BUWpEOPU = BUWpRecU + BUWpBOPU - BUWpSlsU - BUWpShrinkU - BUWpMiscOutU + BUWpMiscInU - BUWpInvAdjU

attribute.name: formula
attribute.value: BUWpRecU = BUWpEOPU - BUWpBOPU + BUWpSlsU + BUWpShrinkU + BUWpMiscOutU - BUWpMiscInU + BUWpInvAdjU

attribute.name: description
attribute.value: When defining editable % contribution measures, it is currently not possible to give them a meaningfull label. By creating a % contrib measure which is equal to the source measure and basing the editable % contribution on this new measure we are working around the label limitation. Last thing to do is make the editable % contrib measure visible in a workbook, but not its source measure.
